# Background Stock Analyzer

Multi-LLM parallel stock analysis with technical, fundamental, and sentiment perspectives.

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Parse ticker symbol(s) and analysis scope
# 2. Create: .context/stock-analysis/
# 3. Determine round: R01, R02, ...
# 4. Write analysis request with context
# 5. Run analysts in background → {round}-{name}.md
# 6. Track agent completion automatically
# 7. Merge into investment thesis when all complete
```

## Output Convention

```
.context/stock-analysis/
├── R01-request.md                # Analysis request and context
{{- range .agents.roles.stock_analyzer }}
├── R01-{{ .name }}.md{{ " " }}            # {{ .provider }}: {{ .for }}
{{- end }}
├── R01-merged.md                 # Round 1: merged analysis
└── R02-merged.md
```

**Round number** increments each analysis iteration:
```bash
mkdir -p .context/stock-analysis
ROUND=$(printf "R%02d" $(( $(ls .context/stock-analysis/R*-*.md 2>/dev/null | sed 's/.*\/R\([0-9]*\)-.*/\1/' | sort -rn | head -1 | sed 's/^0*//') + 1 )))
```

